post_text:
**Urgent Information** - Tuesday, August 11, 2020

All students will be dismissed from school today at 1 PM. There will be no after school care provided.

All Southwest Parke schools will operate on an e-learning schedule for the rest of this week and all of next week. Students will return to face-to-face instruction on Monday, August 24th.

We are moving to this e-learning schedule due to COVID cases and suspected COVID cases that are presenting at this time within our students and staff. We are working with our local health department and neighboring health departments to ensure that contract tracing can be accomplished. During this schedule change, I encourage you to keep practicing social distancing, keep washing your hands, and keep wearing masks in order to reduce possible spread of the virus.

Please know our number one priority is the health and safety of our students. We will continue to monitor this situation and provide you with updates on a regular basis.

Today I had the privilege of honoring those who are retiring from Southwest Parke at the close of our school year.

Brenda Wilhite is retiring after 29 years of serving the students and staff of Montezuma Elementary School. Mrs. Wilhite has served as the secretary and treasurer of the building and has enjoyed seeing everyone everyday. As she steps into her next phase of life, she will likely be more busy trying to keep up with her nine grandchildren.

post_text:
Tomorrow and Thursday we will be distributing food. Food may be picked up at Montezuma Elementary School and Rosedale Elementary School between 11 AM and 12 PM. Food may be picked up at the Old School in Mecca, the firehouse in Lyford, and in front of the General Store at Bridgeton at 11:30 AM.

At every site, please help us all stay safe and healthy by practicing social distancing. If you are in a car, SUV, truck or van, please stay inside your car. Just open the trunk or back deck lid and our people will put the food in directly in your car. Please do not exit your vehicle or congregate at food distribution sites. We want to keep this process moving and keep everyone safe.

I ask that you please be patient with us as we undertake this food distribution program. We are going to do our best to provide for all of our students, and this is a huge undertaking for us. There will likely be some bumps along our path. Rest assured we will be watching day one very carefully and making notes of all the things we can do to make the rest of our days even better.

post_text:
All Southwest Parke schools will be closed tomorrow - Tuesday, November 19 - so that teachers may participate in the Red for Ed Action Day at the Indiana Statehouse.

The Indiana State Teachers Association organized this Red for Ed Action Day, and teachers from all across the state will be participating in this historic event. The action day is intended to make legislators aware of continuing concerns with the current teacher compensation model, excessive and punitive state testing, and professional growth requirements that focus on matters unrelated to classroom instruction and improvement.

Thank you for accommodating tomorrow’s school closure.
